<div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/02/22/downton-abbey-recap-yes-its-called-the-hornby-hotel/" data-title="&#8216;Downton Abbey&#8217; Recap: Yes, It&#8217;s Called the Hornby Hotel" data-description="And the dinner party where the anti-Semite Susan MacClare, Marchioness of Flintshire is silenced.">
